HOW DO YOU INSTALL THE DAMN THING?

The EScanner file can go anywhere, but "golded:scanners" would be
sensible (for GoldEd 4 - "golded:Tools/Scanner" for version 3, I think).

Although EScanner was written originally for GoldEd 3, and it works fine
with it, I found it quite difficult to install it in a way that GoldEd
could actually remember.  I managed it in the end, but I can't remember
how I did it!  :-)

In version 4, you have to call the FUNC SMART command, click the "Mode"
button, and hit "Add".  Open the EScanner file with the file requester,
then type "#?.e" into the pattern string gadget.  Finally, save the
config.  That's it.



